===Etymology===
From [[Middle English]] from [[Old French]] {{term|palais|lang=fr}}, which comes from {{etyl|la}} {{term|Palatium|Palātium|lang=la}}, in reference to the [[Palatine]] Hill, one of the seven hills of Rome, where the aristocracy of the Roman [[republic|Republic]] and—later, Roman emperors—built large, splendid residences.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|/'pæləs/}}
* {{audio|en-us-palace.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Official [[residence]] of a [[head of state]] or other [[dignitary]], especially in a [[monarchical]] or [[imperial]] governmental system.
# A large and [[lavish]]ly [[ornate]] residence.
# A large, ornate [[public]] building used for entertainment or exhibitions.

